		- Repeat Gadget in settings window (KeyRepDelay/KeyRepspeed)
		  now works and included in Prefs file
		- Included PositionsEditor, early stage, GFX refresh
		  from Mainscreen Patternnumber/BPM buggy, but functionable

21.06.1996 @{fg shine}PT3.57@{fg text}

		this Version is made to stabilise all functions and all is
		tested before spreaded
		(args, how many bugs from 1.1 code has Cryptoburners
		forgotten to remove)

		- fixed severall Refresh errors in PattRfsh
		- fix 3 little bugs in Block effects code if patternnumbers
		  over 99 patterns are used
		- implemented increase/decrease Pattern in POS
		- several POS implementations/fixes to V3 standart
		  ĝ show correct position if same pattern plays doubled
		  ĝ position/offset now in 4 digits
		  ĝ refresh now asynchronous, more speed
		- Message by pressing Space and Sampler is active
		  was not stored, fixed
		- patterngadget up function in Mainscreen was trashed. fix
		- DirWindow (LALT D) and SetupWindow (LALT -)now remembers
		   other open Windows and go back if Window is closed
		- find long standing bug in DirWin, it trashed by open if
		  other cia resources also hardpatched. fix
		- Screen Switching with Togglegadget (right top on screen)
		  now works with all open windows
		- All delay loops from V3.15 removed, up/down gadgets
		  debugged, think now all routines use the OS compatible
		  _LVOWait command
		- increase/decrease Songposition (LALT cursor right/left)
		  now refreshes the visible patterns, also in PosED
		- optimations in code for more speed on 7MHz AMigas
		- In follow that PT loads as fast as possible (compact for
		  minimal Amigas) the following changes made:
		  ĝ keyboard US-engl/German now internal changeable in
		    Setup, external pt.keymap load removed
		  ĝ all libraries are loaded if they needed, not by start
		- Length/Pattern/Pos in InfoWindow now are refreshed by
		  playing, same in PosED
		- Loading of old SoundTracker Songs (I mean Songs, not
		  MODS!) now works
		- due the fact of rewriting some code to object orientated
		  writing compacts the code
		- Cleaning up all GUI GFX layouts to standart colors,
		  fix some GFX bugs from Cryptoburners (i.e. Screen toggle
		  Gadgets by other BG Color than black ugly)
		- Volume up/down (LALT .,) also active in PLST/PED etc.
		- Pathname Gadget produces no more trash if pathname
		  longer than 31 chars clicked and you will back

22.06.1996 @{fg shine}PT3.58@{fg text}
		More bugfixes reported and fixed (THX to Neurodancer)
		- effect commands on fast Amigas are not correct setted
		  in Track 1-3
		- if keyrepeat on Info tables produces text trash if
		  cursorkeys pressed
		- XPK Loading is now an asynchronous task (faster)

23.06.1996
		- Due the cursorkey doubles the viewtoggler in PosED
		  now on SPACE instead the cursorkeys
		- PT now 100Pattern-compatible. Mods, Songs etc now
		  loadable, saveable, editable ...
		  100Patternmod is the specialformat from Peter Hannings
		  Mushroom-Protracker (V2.X). In normalmode you can use
		  64, in the 'new mode' 100
		  If you see status display the notekey, PT is in 64Mode,
		  if you see an '!' you are in 100Mode. If you have set
		  100Patternmode in Setup/Maxpatterns, 'old' 64mods now
		  automatic converted to mushroom-format.
		- some minor bugfixes in the Patternscroller
		- Switching different disks in PLST now clears whole PLST
		  screen
		- AutoInsertEffects now normal with LALT I usuable 24.06.1996
		- Removed all keyboard qualifier clearers, so you can
		  use more than one function by pressed qualifiers, e.g.
		  first LALT D, holding LALT, than LALT S
		- Protrackers GUI Refresh now better, no flickering
		  from time etc if Pos, Help, PLST, PED or Info is open
		- fixed some nasty bugs in the Songsave-routines
		- moving from screen finally included, if you press
		  left mousebutton in any screen in the top of Protracker
		  you can move whole screen
		- an little copyright message window if you click on the
		  left top for all who thinks they can made money with
		  our work
		- fixed some nasty bugs in DirScreen, e.g. if many Direntries
		  in an directory (c.a 100) Protracker has freezed
		- Now you can set the keyboard driver method in Setup between
		  USA (US-english) GER (German) and EXT (external keymap)
		- If you switch to EXT, the old S:pt.keymap is used
		- fixed the no memory Window
		- fixed bug if not enough memory for PLST
		- crunched Songs with PACK and PAKK method now loadable
		- StarTracker mods now loadable (only sample mods)
		- reincluded again the loadroutine for xpk-packed songs
		- added new watchdog to preverse uncoordinated freezings
		  from PT in some situations

21.06.1996 @{fg shine}PT3.59@{fg text}

		- Due the enhacements i must rewrite most screenredraw
		  code, now all combinations of gadgets/windows etc
		  now be usuable (and a bit faster i think)
		- most GUI GFX now internal IFF instead the outdated
		  Bytekiller packed RAW stuff
		- fixed some bugs in Prefs (e.g. Showdate inverted)
		- added better Modcheck by loading: before if you load
		  converted mods sometimes mods ar not accepted
		  (e.g. with samplenames of 17 Bytes instead 16 such as
		  thoose mods from Newtracker)
		- Song print now available to everly device (little bug)
		- prepared for load and save Exe/Track/Inst
		  (not finished in Beta)
		- write an correct Copperlist for ALL Amigas (also AGA)
		  and removed hardcoded ECS switch on AGA-Amigas. I hope
		  the reported spriteproblems on some GFX-cards now
		  ok (please report if not, i can only test on my private
		  machines). nice effect: drawing with double bandwith
		  is now much faster
		- fixed direct adressing modes if songs crunched in old
		  PACK format, crashes my machine sometimes after ending PT

06.07.1996 @{fg shine}PT3.59@{fg text}

		- implementation of the new IFF MODL format, if you switch
		  in settings 'msave' on, the new format is saved instead
		  the older.
		  The new format implements an very easy usage of modules
		  and songs, so revisionshistory, save of all relevant
		  parameters of the file inside etc. Read the fileformat
		  doc inside this archive for more infos.
		- Option window 7 is now implemented for the usage of
		  the advanced IFF Modfile settings
		- fixed some overlay bugs in the window structure. Was
		  sometimes crashed if PT is heavy used (IFF depacker)
		- Fixed GUI errors in setup (SoftIRQ gadget)
		- NTSC scroll works again (i has rewritten some parts of
		  the Copperlist writeroutine some times ago) and has snapped
		  the rastervecs for screen cutting by 200 lines)
		- Changed whole mainscreen decent: sort all buttons for
		  better style, switch volumeslider on the left side
		  from the scopes
		- optimize some parts in patternredraw, some notes are not
		  played by BPMTempo over ca. 150 BPM
		- rewritten some code from automatic DMA wait, now on my
		  test equipment (A4000/060 and A1200/Blizzard 1230 II)
		  all speed params work stable (hope i don't need to im-
		  plement thoose lame DMA wait param, i hate loops)
		- fixed No MOD and No Date in Prefs (has it excluded by
		  searching the directory freeze bug from 3.57)
		- 100 Pattern mods now correct converted in new IFF format
		- Maestro 16Bit-Samples now always usuable, the headercheck
		  in PT was hardcoded for the Maestro software. Now you
		  can use converted Maestro Soundfiles, e.g from SoundBox
		- recoded some parts of the directory structure to remove
		  the limit of 32 chars in DirWin. Now the path can be
		  much longer :-)
		- Changed the PT.config structure for using dynamic chunks.
		  For the future i can added prefs and you can load the
		  old prefs files [loader]. All Protracker V3 configurations
		  now compatible
		- Fixed bug that trashes PT if wrong configfile loaded
		- author search routine has searched by copyright msg
		  in samples (author) only on the first digits, now
		  whole samplename was scanned
		- overwritten amigaguide
		- Fixed flickering of samples in Samplewindow by pressing
		  notekey (numeric keypad)
		- changed Analyzer bars to hires
		- overwritten caching system in Dirwin and Prefsfile, by
		  removing the 30char patternlengthlimit i forgot the
		  limits of this
		- all Packetfield bits in IFFMods now have right values.
		  Default patternmatching in Prefs now #? instead #?MOD#?
		- shorten the FREE text in Dirwin, my 2 Gig HD trashes
		  by large amounts of free space (over 99MB) the digits
		- implemented IFF-Format for Songs
		- Fixed bug by changing Samplelengths, decreasing
		  samples was trashed, increasing has cleared sample

		- New extensions:
		  old module:  mod.
		  old sound:   st.
		  new module:  ptm.
		  new sound:   pts.  (hiliting in Dirwin with opt no .mod)

		- Print PLST (Preseteditor) now works

12.07.1996 @{fg shine}PT3.60a@{fg text}

		- reworked whole code for PhxAss due the fact that most
		  other assemblers not worked 100% with pre-optimized
		  code and a large amount of external datas. Thanks again
		  for a great scene-product
		- reworked this funny amigaguide
		- fixed a bug in startup code who crashed 68000er Amigas
		- implemented double buffering of redraw patterns for
		  speedup
		- optimized 68030er version with speedups in sampler,
		  patterneditor ...
		- Moved Savemodform gadget from Setup in DirScreen
		- startupcode has crashed 68000er machines sometimes,
		  reworked and separate 68000er version included
		  (I HATE to work with rotate loops due the fact that
		  the 68k mnemonic don't know divu.l before 68020)

17.07.1996 @{fg shine}PT3.61 Beta 2@{fg text}

		- setting the rate for samples with LALT+KEYPAD now works
		  always, not only if keyboard percussion (key \) is on
		- removed bug in 100Pattern-Mode if no samples/mod is
		  loaded and you edit notes in pattern Protracker has locked
		- Gadget 'Waveform' in Sampler has had wrong values
		- Samples can now max 131KB long
		- removed GFX trash in PosED if background other than black,
		  added 3D-gadgets for screen/windowswitchers
		- if you load/save configurations from Setupmenu the paths
		  no more trashed for Dirscreen, they are now actualized
		  from the setup settings
		- PT now has real big/low characters everywhere! New font,
		  new national characters
		- clearing the first two bytes from everly sample by loading
		  an module; this is if you ever has had an module with an
		  ugly high beep at the end of sample (buggy converters or
		  lame PC-Trackers who 'can save PT modules')
		- old or buggy converted MODs with an Sample Replen < 2
		  has trashed Protracker by playing this sample first time.
		  Now checked by Loading Samples/Mods and fixed if possible.
		- Samplenamenlength now fully editable with 22 ASC's, all
		  Protrackers missed this feature and allow only 21 due
		  an buggy ASC input routine who trashed the next byte

		- Drumpadmode (key \) now uses other flags in statusbar:
		  none:    empty
		  mode 1 : 1
		  mode 2 : 2

15.08.1996 @{fg shine}Final@{fg text}

		- Beta 2 - Beta 5 loosing maded changes, was a lot :-//
		- Samples loaded in Dirwin now update his filename contents
		  in lister

		Beta 5 to Final:

		- MOD2SMP (by Hali/Union) now works on all machines
		- Copperlist now works on Non-AGA machines as at AGA
		- Fixed IFFMOD Fileformat foolishs in Comment Chunk
		  (was NOT identical with IFF-Docu for programmers)
		- optimized Sample-Replay for =>68020, now sounds
		  a bit smoother
		- Fixed the long standing swap of FU/FD in Sample Edit (Opt2)
		- Samplenames in DirScreen was not updated if loaded. Fixed.


@endnode

